<HEADLINE>
<P>
U.S.-RUSSIA RELATIONS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 * Re Russia's "nationalistic tone" (March 8): What nation is not 
"nationalistic"? When Soviet internationalism promoted communism, we fought the 
Cold War -- and now we condemn Russian nationalism. Will anything less than 
"uncle" warm us? Will our chill persist until Russia rubber-stamps our own 
national interests? 
</P>
<P>
 G. DE WITT 
</P>
<P>
 Seal Beach 
</P>
</TEXT>
