<HEADLINE>
<P>
MICHAEL MILKEN 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Re "Regents' Panel Insists UC Seek Way Out of Deal With Milken," March 18: 
</P>
<P>
 The UC regents, believing that Michael Milken is evil incarnate, have kept a 
$3.3-million gift from him anyway? The regents need only to look in a mirror to 
see who compromised UCLA's integrity. The hypocrisy of the regents' actions 
suggest the problem is not with Milken, but with the embarrassment UCLA faces 
admitting that a university which markets itself as a premier business school 
cannot even negotiate a favorable business contract.These taped lectures are 
marketable only because Milken gave them. Five percent of something is a whole 
lot better than 5% of nothing. 
</P>
<P>
 MARY ANN DUGGAN 
