<P>
2 RUSSIAN SUBMARINES GRAZE WITHOUT DAMAGE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Two Russian nuclear submarines grazed each other during an exercise in the 
northern Barents Sea without causing damage or casualties, the Russian navy 
said Thursday. 
</P>
<P>
 Both boats returned to base after the accident Wednesday, the navy's press 
service said in a short statement. 
</P>
<P>
 The ITAR-Tass news agency said the two submarines had nuclear weapons aboard. 
The navy said the submarines, along with their weapons, sustained no damage and 
there were no radiation leaks. 
</P>
