<HEADLINE>
<P>
METROPOLITAN DIGEST / LOS ANGELES COUNTY NEWS IN BRIEF: ARCADIA; OFFICIAL'S SON 
QUESTIONED IN REMOVAL OF CHALLENGER'S SIGN 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The son of a councilman seeking reelection in April is under investigation for 
allegedly removing an election sign of an opponent of his father's, according 
to police. 
</P>
<P>
 Robert Fasching, son of Councilman George Fasching, is one of three young 
adults the police interviewed in relation to the removal of a campaign sign for 
challenger Sheng Chang from a lawn in Cortez Road area Saturday, said Capt. 
Dave Hinig. No one has been arrested, but investigations are continuing into 
the removal of other Chang signs, Hinig said. 
</P>
