METROPOLITAN DIGEST / LOS ANGELES COUNTY NEWS IN BRIEF: LONG BEACH; SHIPYARD 
GETS CONTRACT ON 3 FRIGATES LEASED TO TAIWAN 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Workers at the Long Beach Naval Shipyard will refurbish three Navy frigates 
that will be leased to Taiwan, a spokesman for an Orange County congressman 
said Thursday. 
</P>
<P>
 In an agreement worth several million dollars, Taiwan will pay for any repairs 
needed on the frigates Joseph Hewes, Cook and Barbey, said Dale Neugebauer, a 
spokesman for Rep. Dana Rohrabacher (R-Huntington Beach).  
</P>
<P>
 The shipyard was targeted in 1991 and 1993 in the ongoing rounds of military 
base closures but was spared both times. 
