<HEADLINE>
<P>
COLLEGE BASKETBALL / POSTSEASON TOURNAMENTS; WOMEN'S NCAA ROUNDUP; DEFENDING 
CHAMPION TEXAS TECH FALLS TO ALABAMA 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 It was just a matter of time before Texas Tech was finished. Sheryl Swoopes 
isn't there anymore. 
</P>
<P>
 The Red Raiders could have used Swoopes, last season's player of the year, 
Thursday night in a 73-68 loss to Alabama at Austin, Tex., in the semifinal 
game of the Midwest Regional. 
</P>
<P>
 Yolanda Watkins scored 17 points for the Crimson Tide, who used superior 
quickness to run defending national champion Texas Tech (28-5) out of the 
tournament. 
</P>
<P>
 An 18-8 burst by sixth-seeded Alabama (25-6) at the outset of the second half 
established control. 
</P>
<P>
 Alabama will play top-seeded Penn State on Saturday night in the regional 
finals. The Nittany Lions (28-2) were 64-60 winners over Seton Hall (27-5). 
EAST REGIONAL 
</P>
<P>
 North Carolina didn't have Charlotte Smith because of her ejection for 
fighting in a victory over Old Dominion on Sunday, but the Tar Heels (30-2) 
didn't need her in a 73-69 victory over Vanderbilt (25-8) at Piscataway, N.J. 
</P>
<P>
 Tonya Sampson hit a go-ahead layup with 1:28 to play, and No. 4 North Carolina 
scored the final 11 points to earn the right to play Connecticut (30-2), a 
78-64 winner over Southern Mississippi (26-5), for the region championship and 
Final Four berth. 
</P>
<P>
 Sylvia Crawley had 22 points for North Carolina and held Vanderbilt's 
6-foot-10 center, Heidi Gillingham, to 13. 
</P>
</TEXT>
