<P>
MOTOR SPORTS; ARENACROSS TO DEBUT IN ANAHEIM 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Arenacross, an indoor version of motocross, will be introduced to the Southern 
California motor racing scene this weekend at Anaheim Arena. 
</P>
<P>
 Jimmy Gaddis, last year's 125cc Western Regional motocross champion, and Pedro 
Gonzales, runner-up in the Anaheim Stadium motocross in January, are 
entered.Racing will begin at 7:30 tonight and Saturday with amateurs riding at 
9 a.m. Sunday. 
</P>
<P>
 Other weekend racing: 
</P>
<P>
 MOTORCYCLES -- The Glen Helen/Prairie Dog Grand Prix will be Saturday over a 
12-mile course at Glen Helen Park in San Bernardino. 
</P>
<P>
 SPRINT CARS -- Sprint Car Racing Assn. drivers will be at the Imperial County 
Fairgrounds in El Centro with IMCA modified stock cars Saturday night. 
</P>
<P>
 STOCK CARS -- Cajon Speedway in El Cajon will open its season Saturday night 
with a 100-lap NASCAR Featherlite Southwest Tour event. . . . Sportsman and pro 
stocks will race Saturday night at Blythe Speedway. 
</P>
<P>
 MISCELLANY -- More than 60 cars are expected Saturday for the ninth annual La 
Carrera Classic vintage Mexican road race. . . . Round 2 of the Polaris Jet 
Sports Grand Prix for watercraft is scheduled Saturday and Sunday at Long Beach 
Marine Stadium. 
</P>
