<P>
PREP ROUNDUP; STYLES, KOVACS LEAD ARTISTS IN VOLLEYBALL 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Dan Styles and Szlirad Kovacs each had 11 kills as visiting Laguna Beach swept 
Trabuco Hills in three games in a Pacific Coast League boys' volleyball match 
Thursday at Trabuco Hills.  
</P>
<P>
 Laguna Beach, the third-ranked team in Orange County, won 15-5, 15-1, 15-2, to 
improve to 4-0, 2-0 in league. Kovacs also had 11 blocks. 
</P>
<P>
 Trabuco Hills is 4-2, 1-1. 
</P>
<P>
 In another Pacific Coast League match: 
</P>
<P>
