WEST VENTURA FOCUS: CAMARILLO; CONTRACT OF BUSINESS CONSULTANT EXTENDED 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By J.E. MITCHELL 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A business development consultant, whose contract was set to expire this 
month, has been rehired by the Camarillo City Council to serve the city for the 
remainder of the year. 
</P>
<P>
 The council voted unanimously Wednesday to extend the contract of Thomas E. 
Flavin, a principal of Business Government Partnership Inc., through 
December.He was hired by the city in October at a cost of $7,500 and will be 
paid an additional $7,500 for the contract extension. 
</P>
<P>
 Council members said they were pleased with Flavin's work and may decide to 
increase his consulting hours starting next year. 
</P>
<P>
 "I'm very impressed with his work and his approach," Councilwoman Charlotte 
Craven said. "I would like to see us increase his services to the city." 
</P>
<P>
 In a report to the city dated March 7, Flavin said he has had talks with 76 
businesses and of those, eight firms have expressed serious interest in 
relocating to the city. 
</P>
<P>
 Flavin did not disclose the names of the businesses considering a move. 
</P>
<P>
 Council members, fearing the city was losing its job base, voted last fall to 
hire Flavin, a Camarillo resident who works out of Burbank. J.E. MITCHELL 
</P>
