<P>
EAST VENTURA FOCUS: THOUSAND OAKS; DONORS BOOST ARTS PLAZA ENDOWMENT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By STEPHANIE SIMON 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The endowment fund supporting Thousand Oaks' Civic Arts Plaza has topped $3.6 
million, as corporate and individual contributions pick up now that the grand 
opening is just seven months away. 
</P>
<P>
 Rockwell International, represented locally by the Rockwell Science Center in 
Thousand Oaks and the Rocketdyne rocket engine plant in Canoga Park, on 
Thursday pledged $100,000 to the cultural center.To recognize the gift, 
Rockwell's name will be affixed to a set of box seats in the balcony. 
</P>
<P>
 In a flurry of new pledges announced this week, Bank of America upgraded its 
donation from $30,000 to $50,000. The additional gift qualifies the corporation 
for membership in the Founders Circle, a club of major donors with special 
ticket privileges. 
</P>
<P>
 Other recent additions to the Founders Circle include: Westlake Village 
resident Mark Mahone; alliance campaign chairman Stephen Woodworth and his 
wife, Robin; and theater Commissioner Harry Selvin and his wife, Gerelda. 
</P>
<P>
 Founders Circle Chairman Larry Janss recently challenged the Alliance for the 
Arts to raise its endowment goal from $3 million to at least $7 million . 
STEPHANIE SIMON 
</P>
