<HEADLINE>
<P>
* ROBERT C. EMBRY; EDUCATOR, CIVIL SERVANT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Robert C. Embry, a longtime professor of business at Cal Lutheran University 
in Thousand Oaks and a former chairman of Ventura County's Civil Service 
Commission, died Thursday after a long battle with lung cancer. He was 58. 
</P>
<P>
 As head of the Civil Service Commission, Embry oversaw the administration of 
the county employee civil service merit system. He was appointed to the 
commission in December, 1986, and served until May, 1993, when he stepped down 
due to his illness. 
</P>
<P>
 Embry's wife, Donna, said he particularly enjoyed teaching. He taught several 
business courses at Cal Lutheran, and had previously worked 26 years as a 
teacher and administrator in the Simi Valley Unified School District. 
</P>
<P>
 Embry, a Thousand Oaks resident, was a family man who was deeply involved in 
community activities, Donna Embry said. 
</P>
<P>
 He is survived by his wife of 32 years, sons Kenneth and Michael, and a 
granddaughter. 
</P>
<P>
 Arrangements are being handled by Pierce Brothers Griffin Mortuary, Thousand 
Oaks. 
</P>
</TEXT>
