<HEADLINE>
<P>
EXECUTIVE SUITE: MCA APPOINTS AL TELLER TO SENIOR EXECUTIVE POST 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 In a move that was anticipated for weeks, MCA Inc. elevated music chief Al 
Teller to corporate executive vice president and signed him to a new long-term 
agreement. 
</P>
<P>
 Teller, 49, joins three others in an elite group of senior executives at the 
Universal City-based entertainment conglomerate that make up something of an 
inner circle, helping MCA Chairman Lew R. Wasserman and President Sidney J. 
Sheinberg plot strategy. 
</P>
<P>
 Others holding the corporate executive vice president title are MCA 
Enterprises chief Skip Paul, motion picture chief Tom Pollock and Tom 
Wertheimer, who oversees television. 
</P>
<P>
 Teller, who retains the title of chairman of the MCA Music Entertainment 
Group, is the first music executive to hold the corporate-level title. In a 
statement, Sheinberg said the move recognizes Teller's "superior performance in 
guiding and expanding" the company's music business and his role "as a member 
of the core group of senior executives of the company." 
</P>
<P>
 * Brian Siberell, formerly vice president of HBO Showcase, joins Creative 
Artists Agency as an agent in the made-for-TV movie department. 
</P>
<P>
 * Walt Disney Pictures has promoted Tim Engel to the newly created position of 
senior vice president, production, for feature animation. 
</P>
<P>
 * Brett Chapman, senior counsel at the Walt Disney Co., has been named vice 
president of business and legal affairs at Buena Vista Home Video Intl. 
</P>
<P>
 * Skouras Pictures has hired William M. Russell as chief financial officer. 
</P>
</TEXT>
