<TEXT>
<P>
 People have been wearing clothes for more than 100,000 years, not just to 
cover themselves, but to improve their appearance, express how they feel and to 
react to their society. To show how clothing reflects the social and economic 
pressures of its time, the Multicultural Awareness Committee of Chapman 
University in Orange presented a fashion show depicting "200 Years of Women's 
Herstory" last week, in honor of Women's History Month. 
