<HEADLINE>
<P>
BEHIND THE SCENES; FOR BEST SUPPORT OF CHARITIES, THE SPOTLIGHT IS ON WINNING 
COMBINATIONS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Academy Awards fever heated up Orange County on Monday as supporters gathered 
to help their favorite charities. 
</P>
<P>
 The 450 people who attended a party for the Assistance League of Newport-Mesa 
received the red carpet treatment at Atrium Court in Fashion Island Newport 
Beach, while 300 people glammed it up at Planet Hollywood in Santa Ana to 
benefit the Cystic Fibrosis Foundation. 
</P>
<P>
 Imitating the glitterati of Hollywood, star-studded locals dressed to pop the 
klieg lights. 
</P>
<P>
 At the Assistance League's "Night of the Stars," women wore a range as wide as 
a 70-millimeter big screen: from two-piece silk pantsuits and short skirts to 
cocktail suits and formal gowns. Men added distinction to their traditional 
black tuxes with colorful cummerbunds and shirts. 
</P>
<P>
 At the Cystic Fibrosis "Evening With Oscar," guests donned hip chic. Armani 
and Versace captured the award for tuxedos with a twist (tieless tuxes in 
green, fuchsia and purple caught the spotlight). Women spent the evening in 
sequins, look-at-me hats and flashy jewelry raided from their safe-deposit 
boxes. 
