<HEADLINE>
<P>
ILLINOIS COURT REJECTS BID TO END ABORTIONS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The state's highest court rejected an attempt Thursday to end abortions at 
Cook County Hospital, which serves many of Chicago's poorest residents. 
</P>
<P>
 The court criticized the four hospital board members who sued to block 
resumption of elective abortions, saying they had "abdicated their legislative 
obligations" by asking the courts to settle the matter. 
</P>
<P>
 Board President Richard Phelan issued an order in 1992 lifting a 12-year ban 
on elective abortions at the public hospital. 
</P>
</TEXT>
