ORANGE COUNTY FOCUS: SANTA ANA; RECEPTION TO RAISE SCHOLARSHIP MONEY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The Hispanic Education Endowment Fund will hold a reception Friday honoring 
the work of the late labor leader, Cesar Chavez, in an effort to help raise 
$100,000 in scholarship money. 
</P>
<P>
 "We're trying to get the Hispanic community mobilized to raise enough seed 
money so local corporations can help us out," said John Reza, a spokesman for 
the endowment fund. 
</P>
<P>
 The reception will be held from 6 to 8:30 p.m. at the Bowers Museum of 
Cultural Art. A minimum $25 donation per person is requested, Reza said. 
