<HEADLINE>
<P>
ORANGE COUNTY FOCUS: WESTMINSTER; SPRING FESTIVAL HOPS INTO CITY ON SATURDAY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 For residents who have not visited the Civic Center in a while, Saturday is a 
good time to come calling. 
</P>
<P>
 Tours of City Hall and other buildings will be conducted all day as part of 
the city's annual spring festival at the Civic Center Gardens on Westminster 
Boulevard.The festival begins at 10 a.m. and ends at 3 p.m. Admission is free. 
</P>
<P>
 A pancake breakfast from 8 to 10 a.m. at the Community Services Building opens 
the day's festivities. The cost of breakfast is $3.50. The proceeds will be 
used to fund activities at the Senior Center. 
</P>
<P>
 During the day, there will be carnival games, pony rides, a petting zoo and 
craft exhibits. The Easter Bunny will visit at noon. 
</P>
<P>
 The Community Services and Recreation Department is sponsoring the spring 
festival. For additional information, call (714) 895-2860. 
</P>
