ORANGE COUNTY FOCUS: SAN CLEMENTE; NOISE FROM EXERCISES AT BASE MAY BE HEARD 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 People living as far as 50 miles from Camp Pendleton -- including many cities 
in South County -- may hear loud explosions or feel rumblings on Sunday from 3 
to 5 p.m. because of base training sessions, officials said Wednesday. 
</P>
<P>
 The explosions will occur as 500-pound bombs are dropped from fixed-wing 
aircraft into the middle of the base, known as the "Zulu impact area," 
officials said in a news release. Depending on weather conditions, sound from 
the explosions could be amplified. 
</P>
<P>
 For more information, contact the base at (619) 725-5043. 
</P>
