<P>
ORANGE COUNTY FOCUS: CYPRESS; CERRITOS MAN DIES IN CRASH WITH BUS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A 67-year-old man was killed Thursday morning when his car crashed into the 
back of an Orange County Transit Authority bus on Lincoln Avenue near Grindlay 
Street, police said. 
</P>
<P>
 Ki Duck Lee of Cerritos was westbound on Lincoln Avenue when his car collided 
with the bus, which was preparing to pull away from a bus stop on the north 
side of the street, said Police Sgt. Ray Peterson. 
</P>
<P>
 Lee suffered head and chest injuries in the 9:30 a.m. accident and was taken 
to La Palma Intercommunity Hospital, where he died a short time later. The bus 
driver and his four passengers were not injured, police said. 
</P>
<P>
 A second OCTA bus was sent to the scene to pick up the four passengers and 
complete the morning route, said OCTA spokesman John Standiford. 
</P>
<P>
 Police said there were no skid marks at the scene of the accident and it is 
unknown how fast Lee was traveling when the accident occurred. 
</P>
</TEXT>
