ORANGE COUNTY FOCUS: IRVINE; FIRM GIVES $50,000 FOR UCI FELLOWSHIP 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Fluor Daniel Inc. has contributed $50,000 to establish the Fluor Daniel 
Graduate Teaching Fellowship in the UC Irvine School of Engineering. 
</P>
<P>
 The contribution is part of a five-year, $250,000 commitment to provide two 
graduate fellowships a year for those studying remediation or waste 
minimization through the school's environmental engineering program. 
</P>
<P>
 The goal of the program is to have an immediate impact on industry's ability 
to address environmental cleanup opportunities, university officials said. The 
School of Engineering is enlisting industrial participants and has planned a 
program of fellowships, industrial team-teaching, laboratory research sharing 
and summer student internships. 
</P>
</TEXT>
