<BYLINE>
<P>
By GREG HERNANDEZ, TIMES STAFF WRITER 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A 34-year-old man was in critical condition Thursday with a gunshot wound to 
the head after he shot his ex-wife's boyfriend in the shoulder and then shot 
himself, police said. 
</P>
<P>
 The shooting occurred moments after Flordelino Aquino barged into the 
apartment of his 33-year-old former wife, Josie Aquino, about 9:45 p.m. 
Wednesday, police Lt. Sam Allevato said. 
</P>
<P>
 The woman's boyfriend, Buddy William Hayes, 43, lives in the same apartment 
complex and was visiting with her when her ex-husband arrived armed with two 
handguns, police said. 
</P>
<P>
 "The two men got into an altercation and there was a struggle for the gun and 
that's when Hayes was shot in the shoulder," Allevato said. 
</P>
<P>
 Hayes ran out into the street in front of the Creek Road apartment and was 
soon met by police officers. Meanwhile, Josie Aquino was inside trying to 
prevent her ex-husband from chasing after Hayes and shooting him again. She was 
not injured, police said. 
</P>
<P>
 "The woman blocked the door so (Aquino) turned the gun to his head and shot 
himself in front of his ex-wife," Allevato said. "She was tending to him when 
paramedics arrived." 
</P>
<P>
 Police recovered both guns near the front door of the apartment. 
</P>
<P>
 The Aquinos, who have two children, had been divorced for about three years. 
Allevato said the woman and her boyfriend had been threatened by her ex-husband 
in the past. 
</P>
<P>
 "We had been called out to the house on previous occasions on disturbances 
caused by the ex-husband," Allevato said. 
</P>
<P>
 Both the gunman and Hayes were taken to Western Medical Center-Santa Ana. 
Hayes is listed in stable condition, a hospital official said. 
