<P>
GLENDALE/BURBANK FOCUS: BURBANK; WORK BEGINS ON CAR-POOL LANES 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By CHIP JOHNSON 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Work began this week on new car-pool lanes on both sides of the Ventura 
Freeway along four miles of road between the Golden State and Glendale 
freeways, authorities said. 
</P>
<P>
 Also, Chumo Construction, the Baldwin Park construction firm that will 
undertake the $4.5-million project, will restripe that portion of the road and 
build a new concrete median between the lanes, according to Caltrans, the state 
transportation agency. 
</P>
<P>
 Most of the work will be done at night, but will require some lane closures, 
the agency said. The project is scheduled for completion early next year. 
</P>
<P>
 The work is part of a 15-year project undertaken by Caltrans, which is working 
to build a network of car-pool lanes across most of Los Angeles County. CHIP 
JOHNSON 
</P>
