<P>
EAST VALLEY FOCUS: VAN NUYS; MAN ARRESTED AGAIN UNDER BAN ON GANGS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By DAVID COLKER 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The first gang member to be convicted of violating the court injunction aimed 
at curbing Blythe Street gang activities is in trouble again. 
</P>
<P>
 Jessie Gonzales, 19, who goes by his gang name of Speedy, was arrested twice 
last week on additional charges that he violated the injunction and also the 
provisions of his probation, according to a statement released Wednesday from 
the city attorney's office. 
</P>
<P>
 These arrests marked his third and fourth since his conviction in August on 
violating the injunction that bans possession of a pager, obstruction of 
traffic and other activities associated with gangs in the Blythe Street area. 
</P>
<P>
 On March 17, according to the statement, police say they spotted Gonzales on 
Chase Street at the northern end of the area defined by the injunction, 
stopping traffic and wearing a pager. 
</P>
<P>
 The next day, Gonzales was arrested on a charge that he entered an area that 
is off limits to him under the terms of his probation. 
</P>
<P>
 A hearing on the latest two arrests is scheduled for April 6 in Van Nuys 
Municipal Court. DAVID COLKER 
</P>
</TEXT>
