<HEADLINE>
<P>
SO WHERE DO YOU FIND ALL THESE HOT IMPROVS? HERE . . . 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By CHUCK CRISAFULLI 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Here are some of the places to find improvisational work in the Los 
Angeles-Orange County area: 
</P>
<P>
 The Acme Comedy Theater: 5124 Lankershim Blvd., North Hollywood. Acme's new 
show, "Acme Survival Kit," plays Friday and Saturday at 8 p.m. There are also 
improv shows Sunday and Thursday. (818) 753-0650. 
</P>
<P>
 Comedysportz: Tamarind Theatre: 5919 Franklin Ave., Hollywood. The group 
performs competitive team comedy improv. Match time is 10:30 p.m. Saturday. 
(213) 856-4796. 
</P>
<P>
 The Alumni Players present "The Harold" at the Improv, 8162 Melrose Ave., West 
Hollywood, Sundays at 8 p.m. (213) 651-2583. 
</P>
<P>
 Groundling Theater: 7307 Melrose Ave., Hollywood. The top Groundlings perform 
in "Groundlings Fondue Party" Friday at 8 p.m. and Saturday at 8 and 10 p.m. 
Their new show, "Gettin' Some," begins April 15. The all-improv "Cooking With 
Gas" takes place Thursdays at 8 p.m. (213) 934-9700. 
</P>
<P>
 L.A. Connection: 13442 Ventura Blvd., Sherman Oaks. The main group performs 
Saturday at 9 p.m., but there are a number of varied lineups and performances 
throughout the week. (818) 784-1868. 
</P>
<P>
 Mice: West Hollywood Playhouse, 666 N. Robertson Ave., West Hollywood. The 
Mice Improv Comedy All-Stars give a free performance every Saturday at 10 p.m. 
Improv workshops are Monday at 8 p.m. (818) 762-7547. 
</P>
<P>
 Off the Wall: Main Showroom, the Improv, 8162 Melrose Ave., West Hollywood. 
The group is celebrating its 15th year of shows at the Improv, and performs 
Monday at 9:30 p.m. (213) 651-2583. 
</P>
<P>
 Orange County Crazies: 115 E. Santa Ana Blvd., Santa Ana. The long-running 
group performs "Orangefeld," its send-up of "Seinfeld," Saturdays at 8 p.m. 
through April 16. (714) 550-9900. 
</P>
<P>
 Oxymoron: Blue Marble Coffeehouse, 1907 Harbor Blvd., Costa Mesa. The improv 
troupe performs every other Wednesday at the coffeehouse, with the next show 
coming up Wednesday at 8 p.m. Free. (714) 646-5776. 
</P>
<P>
 QBalls Improv Comedy: QBalls Billiard Club, 99 E. Colorado Blvd., Pasadena. 
Shows are Wednesday at 8 p.m. (818) 405-9777. 
</P>
<P>
 TheatreSports: Theatre/Theater, 1713 Cahuenga Blvd., Hollywood. Improv shows 
are Monday and Saturday at 8 p.m. "Triple Play" is performed Saturdays at 10:30 
p.m. (213) 469-9689. 
</P>
<P>
 Way Off Broadway: 1058 East 1st St., Santa Ana. The theater company delves 
into improv every few months; the next production begins in May. (714) 
547-8997. 
</P>
<P>
 Wild Side Theater: 10945 Camarillo St., North Hollywood. "Medicine Show," 
Friday at 9 p.m.; "Experimental Show," Friday at 10:30 p.m.; "Instant Show," 
Saturday at 9 p.m.; "Improv We Trust," Saturday at 10:30 p.m. (818) 506-8838. 
</P>
<P>
 Wrought Irony performs Sunday nights at the Laugh Factory, 8001 Sunset Blvd., 
West Hollywood. For times, call (213) 656-1336. 
</P>
<P>
 Cable TV: "Whose Line Is It Anyway?," Comedy Central, Monday-Friday, 1:30 p.m. 
and 9:30 p.m. CHUCK CRISAFULLI 
</P>
